What was the turning point? When did it go from =E2=80=9CGrow
and scale at all costs=E2=80=9D to, =E2=80=9CWait, this isn=E2=80=99t worki=
ng=E2=80=9D?

=C2=A0

That was really Covid for them. That was a big turning point when their sal=
es stopped growing as fast as they had previously, but there wasn=E2=80=99t=
 a big moment where it was like, =E2=80=9COh, this isn=E2=80=99t working.=
=E2=80=9D It was more that Goop had all the hype at the beginning because o=
f Gwyneth, and they were saying the thing that was controversial=E2=80=93=
=E2=80=93but then the
halo of that starts to not be as exciting. They only had Goop Beauty, and G=
oop Beauty has been growing every year, but it=E2=80=99s still just not hug=
e.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Advertising business as a big part of revenue started to decline, and that =
was probably the biggest shift to revenue of the last several years. It was=
 not half of the business, but more than 25 percent at one point. Goop had =
been leaning into it because it
was paying for itself and supporting the growth in Goop=E2=80=99s own brand=
 product categories. They got into the idea of, =E2=80=9CWe can just use th=
is vehicle to pay for the business,=E2=80=9D but in Covid all of those acco=
unts stopped spending. It happened slowly, and at the same time they couldn=
=E2=80=99t rely on their product businesses because they weren=E2=80=99t se=
t up right yet.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

There was no collapse; it=E2=80=99s more that they haven=E2=80=99t
been able to grow because the puzzle has looked different. Revenue has been=
 coming from different places over the years, so there hasn=E2=80=99t been =
this decline, even though revenue has shifted and hasn=E2=80=99t increased =
as much as it should have. There haven=E2=80=99t been any huge missteps.

