230cb7569cabeca7e0afa12c92b" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d400=
00;">The RealReal</a> at a far more swallowable price.=C2=A0</li><li style=
=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Reading the Fashion Week tea leaves</em>: Okay,=
 so I looked at the fashion calendar for the January men=E2=80=99s shows in=
 Milan and Paris, couture, and London. Loewe canceled its men=E2=80=99s sho=
w. J.W. Anderson is not showing men=E2=80=99s in Milan or women=E2=80=99s i=
n London=E2=80=A6 for now. Is
there something to be said here?=C2=A0<br/><br/>Look, in the end, there is =
an increasing likelihood=E2=80=94or at least a <em>very </em>nonzero chance=
=E2=80=94that <strong>Jonathan Anderson</strong>=E2=80=99s last show for Lo=
ewe will be in March, during the women=E2=80=99s collections. (Last week, I=
 put it at an 80 percent likelihood. Now I=E2=80=99m upping it to 95. When =
I know for sure, I will tell you.)=C2=A0<br/><br/>That said, pretty much no=
 one is showing during Milan men=E2=80=99s (the big shows are Prada and Arm=
ani) and I suspect that the
women=E2=80=99s shows are going to be weird this season, too, thanks to a l=
ot of designer changes (<strong>Matthieu</strong> not showing Chanel until =
October, the Oscars hitting right between the Milan and Paris shows, etcete=
ra). I=E2=80=99m sad to miss couture, with Schiaparelli, Ala=C3=AFa, and <s=
trong>Peter Copping</strong>=E2=80=99s debut at Lanvin. Couture is actually=
 the very best time to be in Paris. Yes, I know there are new rumors of cha=
nges at big houses, and you would like me to address them, and I will when =
the
time is right. The one thing I will say, as evidenced in the past couple of=
 weeks: Kering, for all its messiness, continues to be interesting, and LVM=
H, for all its grandiosity, continues to be predictable.=C2=A0</li><li styl=
e=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>The party=E2=80=99s over?</em>: I do hope you =
had fun at all the holiday soir=C3=A9es last week. The ones that popped up =
repeatedly for me=E2=80=94other than D=C3=B4en=E2=80=99s rager at Genghis C=
ohen (yes, <strong>Adam Brody</strong> was there, chill out)=E2=80=94includ=
e <strong>Marisa
Meltzer</strong>=E2=80=99s Upper East Side house party (if you are a writer=
 of a certain age and weren=E2=80=99t there-slash-invited=E2=80=A6 you gott=
a suck up to Marisa more, I guess?), and <strong>Kaitlin Phillips</strong>=
=E2=80=99 company function in the apartment above The River bar in Chinatow=
n. (The space is designed by Green River Project, you can smoke, and appare=
ntly the food is great, too. I=E2=80=99m told the best guest was =E2=80=9Ce=
vil P.R. guy=E2=80=9D <strong>Jim McCarthy</strong> from Counterpoint Strat=
egies.) <em>Everyone </em>in
London showed up to the Dover Street Market 20th anniversary celebration. (=
My favorite photo was of <strong>Katie Grand</strong> sandwiched between <s=
