argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong><em>Rachel Strugatz</em></strong><stron=
g>: What was the
first thing you did when you got in there?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><em>Julia Hunter</em>=
: I=E2=80=99m focusing on topline growth and reducing the size of the team.=
 The company is doing very well from a revenue perspective, but operating e=
xpenses have continued to grow. I know that it=E2=80=99s unpopular to let p=
eople go, but they hired a lot of people that they probably shouldn=E2=80=
=99t have, and that payroll number had gotten very big. There=E2=80=99s bee=
n a
big shift in focus from investors and the market=E2=80=93=E2=80=93it used t=
o be on topline growth and growth at all costs, and now everybody wants pro=
fitability and EBITDA. Goop was very much in the growth-at-all-costs mental=
ity in the moment when the market was crazy. They built up this company bel=
ieving they were going to grow into this valuation, and people thought it w=
as going to be a unicorn quickly. You have to be as lean as you possibly ca=
n when you=E2=80=99re in this environment, and when the company is not
profitable. They=E2=80=99re close=E2=80=93=E2=80=93it=E2=80=99s not like it=
 was losing a lot more before.</p></div>
